<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a7d7e0f elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"a7d7e0f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Natan-768x768.png\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-255\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Natan-768x768.png 768w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Natan-300x300.png 300w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Natan-1024x1024.png 1024w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Natan-150x150.png 150w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Natan.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7a4061a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7a4061a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Natan is an eighth-grader at <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/West-Sound-Academy-143072302405371\/?__tn__=K-R&amp;eid=ARBQoX3JnaR5uInTQBBsWGlM7XxHlDEwth_QGPf10Qni7pbx6NmcyQ9lVha4kwKq2eOblFgPPVH6qgtS&amp;fref=mentions&amp;__xts__%5B0%5D=68.ARBQ9nCzv0ZkuCbHKlgcAysIvZbkFhUII0ERSJ35LqXLPXkofOHVCtvVKt8SkZlySJhXSqhVTTlx9qCp9QTrgFkjZ07HFL2ravmyVQyokFOlVrMk2pmJLhkAT5BYn7V3-omVo5-D-iQE03tsFctUmC4Baa7loymHUV3JP4I85UR-SlXuKeVplpG2-48LCreTDn7Ckf47vRa_QnhI6dkJZr02F28YalhpO5MqIB1_zFNNrVQtaTxrI8G4CdKPWTe5-ILh3HTEba5GxY_7_XHKHsjVL-fnofbku7JSVg6VAEQtLsp9G5cLL82uvMeqh96vs3rfa2U9T3c5qg6D_Na5sGg\" data-hovercard=\"\/ajax\/hovercard\/page.php?id=143072302405371&amp;extragetparams=%7B%22__tn__%22%3A%22%2CdK-R-R%22%2C%22eid%22%3A%22ARBQoX3JnaR5uInTQBBsWGlM7XxHlDEwth_QGPf10Qni7pbx6NmcyQ9lVha4kwKq2eOblFgPPVH6qgtS%22%2C%22fref%22%3A%22mentions%22%7D\" data-hovercard-prefer-more-content-show=\"1\">West Sound Academy<\/a> in Poulsbo, WA. He has lived on Bainbridge Island for 7 years. He is currently on the Bainbridge Island Swim team and enjoys playing bass. In 2019, Natan became a Carson Scholar for his humanitarian actions and academic accomplishments. Natan is part of Raising The Blues, Ltd. which is a non-profit organization helping kids with special needs and unique life challenges through music. Raising The Blues, Ltd. has helped thousands of kids over the last 10 years. Natan has raised over $30,000 for this cause. Raising The Blues, Ltd. is run by Natan and his parents. Natan has volunteered since he was 6 and is now webmaster, volunteer, and fundraiser for Raising the Blues, Ltd.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-77b1321\" data-id=\"77b1321\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c8e39c1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"c8e39c1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Zeya-768x768.png\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-256\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Zeya-768x768.png 768w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Zeya-300x300.png 300w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Zeya-1024x1024.png 1024w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Zeya-150x150.png 150w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Zeya.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-eb55cc7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"eb55cc7\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Zeya is a high school senior at Bainbridge High School. She is passionate about the outdoors, especially hiking and backpacking. She&#8217;s also a dedicated swimmer and was a captain for the high school girls swim and dive team. When she is not swimming or in the outdoors she loves improving her Spanish language skills. Zeya is a peer Spanish tutor at Bainbridge Youth Services and has worked with <span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Bainbridge Ometepe Sister Island Association (BOSIA) for three years as part of the 2018 and 2019 student delegations and as a student board member. After high school she will be attending college to study Spanish.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-inner-section elementor-element elementor-element-b6a66b8 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"b6a66b8\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-7451583\" data-id=\"7451583\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b293b06 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"b293b06\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-juliette-768x768.png\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-262\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-juliette-768x768.png 768w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-juliette-300x300.png 300w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-juliette-1024x1024.png 1024w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-juliette-150x150.png 150w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-juliette.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-86bcb63 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"86bcb63\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Juliette is a sophomore at BHS and has been a Girl Scout for 10 years. She plays piano and is on the high school tennis and swim teams. Her path to action and service began 3 years ago and she loves the feeling of satisfaction she gets from helping those in need. Some of her activities include helping out at Rotary Auction, fixing trails on a week-long backpacking camp through Washington Trails Association, serving th<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">e homeless in Seattle and locally, volunteering at Girl Scout day camp, tutoring kids in math, and tutoring the elderly in technological issues. She is preparing for a week-long trip to Ensenada, Mexico, where she\u2019ll be building houses for low-income families. She hopes to inspire others to action. <\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-7266966\" data-id=\"7266966\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-76c98d3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"76c98d3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-spencer-768x768.png\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-266\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-spencer-768x768.png 768w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-spencer-300x300.png 300w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-spencer-1024x1024.png 1024w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-spencer-150x150.png 150w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-spencer.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7169c96 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7169c96\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Spencer is a senior at Bainbridge High School who enjoys writing about world affairs and local news. Awarded the Dr. Frank Kitamoto Legacy Award for inclusion, civil rights and social justice earlier this year, he is a student representative on the Multicultural Advisory Council and co-president of the school\u2019s Model UN club. Cross country running, binging Netflix, hanging out with friends, and playing hockey are activities he enjo<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">ys, and he has an incurable addiction to sneakers! <\/span><\/p><p>Get ready to join us on February 1, because he is excited about speaking at TEDxYouth@BainbridgeIsland and wants everyone to gain some knowledge and inspiring takeaways from his talk!<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-inner-section elementor-element elementor-element-c34c547 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"c34c547\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-8fe2dee\" data-id=\"8fe2dee\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-89f53c6 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"89f53c6\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Emilie-768x768.png\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-269\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Emilie-768x768.png 768w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Emilie-300x300.png 300w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Emilie-1024x1024.png 1024w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Emilie-150x150.png 150w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Emilie.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cc3a54d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cc3a54d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Emilie was recently crowned Miss Washington&#8217;s Outstanding Teen 2019 through the Miss American Scholarship Organization. She is an active member of her senior class as Class President at <a class=\"profileLink\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/klahowyasecondaryschool\/?__tn__=K-R&amp;eid=ARAlMQw7SxZbs_GoVUSc_4jjccIqgOf0JdmouLMytNEWPXK3NniZ162g1uXei-eSOYScgwwGxZhmdk7u&amp;fref=mentions&amp;__xts__%5B0%5D=68.ARBcl0WbbYHb22ArAmN46qy1H4mRwqI90KHu9O3a4erD43pP1pQORddTdNc4pHDem-SHtimg35IY8g-ghSTbT_OCSGs-Ql7hQldK5Ybug-MlDY9ENPJOs1hua2sEBcREBxarpHXNRT_NW5vqC7IDG1CE0Z38j1qlvmIGa80e3m1Pvimjsd7eG-4HVDYKbrAO6nx-__oY5LY-EEppUe8pIlRTUDByZ3fmIzsyv5CqiY9BV-EvJANpPx0jDifeR5TcrQeA8HFWxXg9Lz5l5vaeZxZ6q1eb_elqSvgzEBN2BftzkQwiWY-iqzBUc-2k-j_kABA\" data-hovercard=\"\/ajax\/hovercard\/page.php?id=1662638960645194&amp;extragetparams=%7B%22__tn__%22%3A%22%2CdK-R-R%22%2C%22eid%22%3A%22ARAlMQw7SxZbs_GoVUSc_4jjccIqgOf0JdmouLMytNEWPXK3NniZ162g1uXei-eSOYScgwwGxZhmdk7u%22%2C%22fref%22%3A%22mentions%22%7D\" data-hovercard-prefer-more-content-show=\"1\">Klahowya Secondary School<\/a>, ASB Vice President, Leos Club President, Honor Society Vice President, and captain of the cheer squad. Emilie has a passion for service and has visited the Dominican Republic twice on medical mission trips. She has worked closely with several local organizations to challenge global poverty. A ballet dancer for fourteen years, Emilie has trained with the Bolshoi Ballet, Ballet West, and Pacific Northwest Ballet. She spent the summer of 2017 at the Bolshoi Ballet in Moscow on a U.S. State Department scholarship, and the summer of 2019 in Spain on a Lions Scholarship. Emilie has also been classically trained in piano. Next year, she plans to attend college on the pre-med track, continuing her and ballet and music training. Through her TEDx Talk, she hopes to inspire youth to take action by challenging difficulties facing our society.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-8e5e8c5\" data-id=\"8e5e8c5\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-73a3a8f elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"73a3a8f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"768\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Cora-768x768.png\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-276\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Cora-768x768.png 768w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Cora-300x300.png 300w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Cora-1024x1024.png 1024w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Cora-150x150.png 150w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TEDx-Speaker-Cora.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c784b8e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c784b8e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Cora is a junior at Bainbridge High School Bainbridge, a member of BHS Global Health Club, and co-Vice President of the school\u2019s Model United Nations. She is passionate about global affairs and politics, and spends much of her time debating current events with her friends. When she\u2019s not doing homework or running cross country, Cora is baking, watching movies, and listening to music as well as playing the violin! She is delighted and honored to be a part of TEDxYouth@BainbridgeIsland!<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-95cc02f elementor-widget-divider--view-line elementor-widget elementor-widget-divider\" data-id=\"95cc02f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"divider.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-divider\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-divider-separator\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e352775 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e352775\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2><strong>OUR CRITERIA<br><\/strong><\/h2>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Our goal at TEDxYouth@BainbridgeIsland is to present talks on issues that matter to our community and to spark a real dialogue about how to make a difference.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>We seek ideas that are clear, concise, compelling, original and relevant. Our Executive Team collaborated with our Curation Team to review speaker applications, and encouraged applicants to review <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/participate\/organize-a-local-tedx-event\/tedx-organizer-guide\/speakers-program\/what-is-a-tedx-talk\">&#8220;What is a TED talk?&#8221;<\/a> and&nbsp; <a href=\"http:\/\/storage.ted.com\/tedx\/manuals\/tedxcontentguidelines.pdf\">content guidelines<\/a> so they had a clear understanding of what we were looking for.<\/p>\n<p><strong>We are eager to consider ideas&nbsp;that<\/strong>:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Are&nbsp;radically new<\/li>\n<li>Showcase fresh&nbsp;approaches to enduring&nbsp;problems<\/li>\n<li>Challenge&nbsp;our conceptions about&nbsp;what\u2019s possible<\/li>\n<li>Expose us to cutting-edge&nbsp;research, technology or&nbsp;design<\/li>\n<li>Energetically redefine&nbsp;the human experience<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>We reject&nbsp;ideas that are:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vague or underdeveloped<\/li>\n<li>Based on pseudoscience rather than&nbsp;quantifiable and specific data<\/li>\n<li>Purely personal or motivational in nature<\/li>\n<li>Already ubiquitous<\/li>\n<li>Solely about&nbsp;overcoming adversity or obstacles<\/li>\n<li>Motivated by&nbsp;or&nbsp;seek to promote corporate, political, or religious agendas<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Our event took place Saturday, February 1, 2020.&nbsp;Speaker applications were accepted beginning October 4, 2019 and the deadline was November 4, 2019. <\/strong><strong>We made the first batch of speaker selections by November 18, 2019.<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-638736ca elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"638736ca\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-60d00a82\" data-id=\"60d00a82\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6a1d9b8d elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"6a1d9b8d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"560\" height=\"59\" src=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/Screen-Shot-2019-09-19-at-7.36.41-AM.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-image-11\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/Screen-Shot-2019-09-19-at-7.36.41-AM.png 560w, http:\/\/tedxyouthbainbridgeisland.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/Screen-Shot-2019-09-19-at-7.36.41-AM-300x32.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-7ebb326e\" data-id=\"7ebb326e\" data-el